{"type":"text","timestamp":1775863581488,"sessionID":"ses_2864bd410ffePk0iImrsJGDaPG","part":{"id":"prt_d79b511c6001A13OUB3wIU4PRR","messageID":"msg_d79b4adee001CJY5sc31nepl7w","sessionID":"ses_2864bd410ffePk0iImrsJGDaPG","type":"text","text":"Now I'll create a comprehensive tasks.md file for AR-019, breaking down the work into atomic, independently verifiable tasks.","time":{"start":1775863581486,"end":1775863581486}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775863581595,"sessionID":"ses_2864bd410ffePk0iImrsJGDaPG","part":{"id":"prt_d79b7cb31001FcvImXxGGjbdQU","messageID":"msg_d79b4adee001CJY5sc31nepl7w","sessionID":"ses_2864bd410ffePk0iImrsJGDaPG","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-43f609fa21bd4b6b9cad6f3b8ac6a98d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-019 — CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries) Implementation Tasks\n\n**Module**: `cmd`\n**Language**: Go\n**Size**: M\n**Design Stage**: ST-3 Completed\n\n## Task Breakdown\n\n### Task 1: Verify cmd/agentd directory structure and implementation\n- [ ] Verify cmd/agentd directory exists\n- [ ] Verify main.go exists\n- [ ] Verify main.go implements controller-runtime manager initialization\n- [ ] Verify metrics-bind-address flag is defined (default: \":8080\")\n- [ ] Verify health-probe-bind-address flag is defined (default: \":8081\")\n- [ ] Verify leader-elect flag is defined (default: false)\n- [ ] Verify zap logger is initialized\n- [ ] Verify manager is created with proper options\n- [ ] Verify reconciler is registered with manager\n- [ ] Verify health checks are registered (/healthz, /readyz)\n- [ ] Verify signal handlers are configured (SIGINT, SIGTERM)\n\n**Verification**: Run `go build ./cmd/agentd` and verify binary compiles successfully\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Verify cmd/picod directory structure and implementation\n- [ ] Verify cmd/picod directory exists\n- [ ] Verify main.go exists\n- [ ] Verify flags.go exists\n- [ ] Verify main.go implements HTTP server initialization\n- [ ] Verify --port flag is defined (default: \"8080\")\n- [ ] Verify --workspace flag is defined (default: \"\")\n- [ ] Verify klog is initialized\n- [ ] Verify picod.NewServer is called with proper config\n- [ ] Verify signal handlers are configured (SIGINT, SIGTERM)\n- [ ] Verify graceful shutdown is implemented with 30s timeout\n\n**Verification**: Run `go build ./cmd/picod` and verify binary compiles successfully\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Create cmd/workloadmanager directory structure\n- [ ] Create cmd/workloadmanager directory\n- [ ] Create cmd/workloadmanager/main.go\n- [ ] Create cmd/workloadmanager/flags.go\n- [ ] Create cmd/workloadmanager/main_test.go\n- [ ] Verify directory structure matches design\n\n**Verification**: Run `ls -la cmd/workloadmanager/` and verify all files are created\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Implement cmd/workloadmanager/flags.go\n- [ ] Define port flag (default: \"8080\")\n- [ ] Define redis-addr flag (default: \"localhost:6379\")\n- [ ] Define redis-password flag (default: \"\")\n- [ ] Define redis-db flag (default: 0)\n- [ ] Define kubeconfig flag (default: \"\")\n- [ ] Define metrics-bind-address flag (default: \":8080\")\n- [ ] Define health-probe-bind-address flag (default: \":8081\")\n- [ ] Define leader-elect flag (default: false)\n- [ ] Add proper flag documentation\n- [ ] Export getter functions for each flag\n\n**Verification**: Run `./workloadmanager --help` and verify all flags are displayed\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Implement cmd/workloadmanager/main.go - Package and imports\n- [ ] Declare main package\n- [ ] Import context package\n- [ ] Import flag package\n- [ ] Import os package\n- [ ] Import os/signal package\n- [ ] Import syscall package\n- [ ] Import time package\n- [ ] Import github.com/redis/go-redis/v9 package\n- [ ] Import k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes package\n- [ ] Import k8s.io/client-go/rest package\n- [ ] Import k8s.io/client-go/tools/clientcmd package\n- [ ] Import k8s.io/klog/v2 package\n- [ ] Import github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager package\n\n**Verification**: Run `go build ./cmd/workloadmanager` and verify imports are correct\n\n---\n\n### Task 6: Implement cmd/workloadmanager/main.go - Main function initialization\n- [ ] Initialize klog with klog.InitFlags(nil)\n- [ ] Parse command-line flags with flag.Parse()\n- [ ] Create background context\n- [ ] Log startup message with klog.Info\n- [ ] Implement error handling for initialization failures\n- [ ] Add proper error logging with klog.Fatalf\n\n**Verification**: Run binary without flags and verify initialization sequence\n\n---\n\n### Task 7: Implement cmd/workloadmanager/main.go - Redis client initialization\n- [ ] Create Redis client with redis.NewClient\n- [ ] Configure Redis address from flag\n- [ ] Configure Redis password from flag\n- [ ] Configure Redis DB number from flag\n- [ ] Ping Redis to verify connection\n- [ ] Handle Redis connection failure with klog.Fatalf\n- [ ] Log successful Redis connection\n\n**Verification**: Run binary with valid Redis address and verify connection succeeds\n\n---\n\n### Task 8: Implement cmd/workloadmanager/main.go - Kubernetes client initialization\n- [ ] Check if kubeconfig flag is set\n- [ ] If kubeconfig is set, use clientcmd.BuildConfigFromFlags\n- [ ] If kubeconfig is not set, use rest.InClusterConfig\n- [ ] Handle config creation failure with klog.Fatalf\n- [ ] Create Kubernetes clientset with kubernetes.NewForConfig\n- [ ] Handle clientset creation failure with klog.Fatalf\n- [ ] Log successful Kubernetes connection\n\n**Verification**: Run binary with kubeconfig and verify Kubernetes client initializes\n\n---\n\n### Task 9: Implement cmd/workloadmanager/main.go - Server configuration\n- [ ] Create workloadmanager.Config struct\n- [ ] Set Port from flag\n- [ ] Set RedisClient from initialized client\n- [ ] Set K8sClient from initialized clientset\n- [ ] Set MetricsAddr from flag\n- [ ] Set ProbeAddr from flag\n- [ ] Set EnableLeaderElection from flag\n- [ ] Verify all required fields are populated\n\n**Verification**: Review config structure and verify all fields are correctly set\n\n---\n\n### Task 10: Implement cmd/workloadmanager/main.go - Server creation\n- [ ] Call workloadmanager.NewServer with context and config\n- [ ] Handle server creation failure with klog.Fatalf\n- [ ] Log server creation success\n- [ ] Verify server is created with correct configuration\n\n**Verification**: Run binary and v